            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" xml:lang="gez">
                    <note>The text is quoted after<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/FGSB8GYT"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Afawarq1984Yageezqeneyat"/><title level="m">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;የግእዝ ቅኔያት የስነ ጥበብ ቅርስ። ሁለተኛ ክፍል። ንባቡ ከነትርጓሜው (&lt;/hi&gt;Yagǝʾǝz qǝneyāt yasǝna ṭǝbab qǝrs.  Hulataññā kǝfl.  Nǝbābu kannatǝrgwāmew&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, Gǝʾǝz &lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;qǝnes&lt;/hi&gt;, the monument of wisdom. Second part. Reading  with interpretationʼ)&lt;/hi&gt;</title><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʾAfawarq Zawde</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Qaḍalā Mangǝśtu</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos Nabiyu</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Kǝnafa Rǝgb ʾAttālal</t:name></editor><pubPlace>Addis Ababa</pubPlace><publisher>Bǝrhānǝnnā salām māttamiyā bet</publisher><date>1991</date><citedRange unit="item">76</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                    <ab>                                              
                        <l n="1">ለብእሲ፡ ጽሙዕ፡ ኢያረውዮ፡ ቈሪረ፡ ማየ፡ እመ፡ ይሰቲ፡ በሕልሙ።</l>
                        <l n="2">ወኢይባልሖ፡ እምጽምዕ፡ ለሐሊበ፡ ዕጐልት፡ ጣዕሙ።</l>
                        <l n="3">ልምላሜ፡ ጕርዔሁ፡ ያየብስ፡ ዳእሙ።</l>
                        <l n="4">ከማሃ፡ ትድላ፡ ዓለሙ።</l>
                        <l n="5">ዘኢረከባ፡ ይቴክዝ፡ ወዘረከባ፡ ይፃሙ።</l>
                        <l n="6">እምዝኒ፡ መንገለ፡ ዝኒ፡ ለለጌሠሙ፡ ወአሙ።</l>
                        <l n="7">ትትፋለስ፡ ለለጊዜ፡ ወለዐርካኒሃ፡ ተኃድጎሙ።</l>
                        <l n="8">በእንተ፡ ዝኒ፡ ሐነጸ፡ ሀገረ፡ ነፍሱ፡ በደሙ።</l>
                        <l n="9"><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</persName> አንበሳ፡ መስዕ፡ ዘ<placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0341DL">ደብረ፡ ሊባኖስ፡</placeName> ገዳሙ።</l>
                        <l n="10">ወበቅድመ፡ አምላክ፡ ትቁም፡ አስተሰነዐላ፡ ለዓጽሙ።</l>
                        <l n="11"><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</persName> አንበሳ፡ መስዕ፡ ዘ<placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0341DL">ደብረ፡ ሊባኖስ፡</placeName> ገዳሙ።</l>
                    </ab>                    
               
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <div type="textpart" xml:lang="en">
                    <ab>
                        <l n="1">Cool water does not satisfy a man if he drinks it in a dream,</l> 
                        <l n="2">And the taste of milk will not save a calf from thirst,</l>
                        <l n="3">The freshness will only make its throat dry.</l>
                        <l n="4">The delight of this world is like this,</l>
                        <l n="5">The one who has not obtained it, is sad, and the one who has obtained it, is toiling.</l>
                        <l n="6">From this over to that, each morning and (each) year,</l>
                        <l n="7">It moves around all the time leaving its companions behind.</l>
                        <l n="8">Because of this he built the city of his soul with his blood, </l>
                        <l n="9"><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>, the lion of the south, of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0341DL">Dabra Libānos</placeName>, his monastery.</l>
                        <l n="10">You are standing in front of God, having dismissed your leg,</l>
                        <l n="11"><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>, the lion of the south, of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0341DL">Dabra Libānos</placeName>.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
